This article is a presidential proclamation issued by Barack Obama on May 13, 2011, declaring May 15 as Peace Officers Memorial Day and May 15-21 as Police Week. The proclamation recognizes the bravery and sacrifice of public safety officers who risk their lives to keep communities safe. It also acknowledges the tragic wave of police officer fatalities in the past year and the 10th anniversary of the September 11 attacks. The proclamation emphasizes the commitment of the administration to protect law enforcement officers and provide support to their families. It mentions initiatives such as the Preventing Violence Against Law Enforcement and Ensuring Officer Resilience and Survivability (VALOR) program and the mandatory wear policy for bulletproof vests. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to observe these events with appropriate ceremonies and activities and encourages the display of the flag at half-staff on Peace Officers Memorial Day.